    "The method defines a so-called cost-matrix which specifies a reward or a penalty over the classifications of an algorithm.",
    "A core idea behind it is similar to resampling but it does not change the prevalence of the training set directly.",
    "However, a performance evaluation for an imbalanced plankton set reported by Corrêa et al. (2016) demonstrates only minor improvements for cost-matrix in comparison to SMOTE and resampling.",
